        "description": {
          "value": "<p>The bilge gremlin’s presence interferes with nonmagical objects that have moving parts, such as clocks, crossbows, or hinges, within 20 feet of it. Such objects that aren’t being worn or carried malfunction while within the aura, and, if in the aura for more than 1 minute, they cease to function until repaired. If a creature in the aura uses a nonmagical object with moving parts, roll a d6. On a 5 or 6, weapons such as crossbows or firearms misfire and jam, and other objects cease to function. A creature can take its action to restore the malfunctioning object by succeeding on a DC 13 Intelligence check.",
